  "text": "Papain-like cysteine proteases are found in most organisms, including virus [CITATION_1] , bacteria [CITATION_2] , yeast [CITATION_3] , protozoa, plants, and animals [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . These enzymes are produced as inactive precursors with a signal peptide for protein secretion and an auto-inhibitory prodomain to prevent unwanted protein degradation (Figure 1 ; [CITATION_6] . The active protease domain contains the catalytic triad Cys-His-Asn (Figure 1) .",
